normalization_record.normalized_question_text:
As shown in Figure (b), a particle located at the origin $O$ starts vibrating at time $t=0$, generating a simple harmonic transverse wave that propagates along the positive $x$-axis. At time $t_1=0.3\mathrm{s}$, the wave reaches point $P$. If $x_{OP}=6\mathrm{m}$ and $x_{PC}=9\mathrm{m}$, find:
1. the wave speed;
2. the period;
3. the first moment when point $C$ reaches the crest.

